# In the app: Handoff → Reviewer checklist (/review/handoff) + strip under the top bar
# explain prototype vs API data for reviewers.

# Optional: HTTP origin or same-origin path (no trailing slash).
# Leave unset to use bundled mock data in the UI.
# Examples:
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api
VITE_API_BASE_URL=

# Quick local backend matching openapi/openapi.yaml:
#   Terminal A: npm run mock:api
#   Terminal B: VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080 npm run dev

# When VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api, forward /api → backend during `npm run dev`:
# VITE_DEV_API_PROXY=http://localhost:8080

# Optional bearer token for authenticated routes (future).
# VITE_API_TOKEN=

# --- Server-only secrets (never VITE_*). Used by `npm run mock:api`.
# Copy `env.local.template` → `.env.local` and paste keys there (gitignored).
# NGX_PULSE_API_KEY=   → live NGX ASI / top gainer on /v1/market/ticker
# OPENAI_API_KEY=     → POST /v1/copilot/chat { "prompt": "..." }

# Supabase (Vite — exposed to browser; use publishable or anon key only)
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
#
# Top-bar Sign in uses Supabase Auth (email + password). In the Supabase
# dashboard: Authentication → Providers → enable Email.

# Apply DB migration: Supabase Dashboard → SQL → paste
# `supabase/migrations/20260406140000_chd_health.sql`, or after `supabase link`:
#   supabase db push

# RAG (server mock API + `npm run rag:seed`): apply migration
# `supabase/migrations/20260406150000_rag_chunks.sql`, then add:
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<service role — never in Vite / browser>
# Then: npm run rag:seed

# Profiles + auth.uid() RLS (run in SQL Editor):
#   supabase/migrations/20260406160000_profiles_rls.sql
# Existing accounts created before this migration may need a manual profile row.

# PDF → RAG: top bar "PDF" (needs API). POST /v1/rag/upload-pdf (multipart field: file).
# Archive copy in Supabase Storage — run in SQL Editor:
#   supabase/migrations/20260406170000_rag_pdf_storage.sql
# Bucket: chd-rag-archives · paths like ingests/<timestamp>_<name>.pdf

# --- Docker (hosted API on your machine / server)
# Requires Docker Desktop (or Engine) running. Use `.env.local` for secrets.
#
#   npm run docker:up      # build + start API on :8080 in background
#   npm run docker:down    # stop
#
# Or one-off:
#   npm run docker:api
#   docker run --env-file .env.local -p 8080:8080 chd-api
#
# Then: VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080 npm run dev
